deck: The origin of the Ice King?
description:
Plot Summary

To abate his loneliness, the Ice King decides that a display of his musical talents is what's needed to attract a princess. Who better to help him than Marceline? However, during the recording session, details are revealed about the connection between these two characters. Will these revelations mean a change of heart for the Ice King, or will he continue to be as annoying as ever?
name: I Remember You

description:
Plot Summary

Cuber, our strange but friendly host from the future, present another five short Ooo stories, based around a common theme. Jake finds an old tome he believes to be an ancient spell book, Marceline goes in search of a legendary guitar, Tree Trunks is offended by what appears to be an obscene gesture, Ice King tries to marry his foot, and BMO imparts some more real life wisdom to it's reflection.
name: Five More Short Graybles

description:
Plot Summary

Finn and Jake are playing frisbee when their disc gets stuck in a tree. Rather than have Jake stretch to retrieve it, Finn takes on the challenge and decides to go up there himself. On the way, he meets many helpful woodland creatures - but are they all that they seem to be?
name: Up a Tree

description:
Plot Summary

Finn is given a mysterious bag, and inside finds a large amount of tiny creatures, each a miniature replica of an inhabitant of Ooo. But he soon becomes fixated on the smaller, moving versions of his friends and loved ones, and starts to spend all of his time manipulating their lives.
name: All the Little People

description:
Plot Summary

The time has come for Lady Rainicorn to give birth! It is an exciting time for Jake, but also an anxious one. Worried that he will not be a good enough father, he seeks guidance from a parenting manual his mother prepared while she was still alive.
name: Jake the Dad

description:
Plot Summary

In an attempt to get away from notoriety and live a quiet life, Finn begins wearing a disguise and referring to himself as Davey. But it isn't long before the persona begins to take over his mind, blurring the line between Finn and Davey.
name: Davey

description:
Plot Summary

Finn is taken aback when his hat suddenly becomes sentient. How did it happen, and what does it want?
name: Little Dude

description:
Plot Summary

The Ice King captures the princesses, and forces them to listen to another of his Fionna and Cake fan fiction stories. When he has finished, Marceline reveals that she has been listening, and decides to tell a story of her own. Marceline's story revolves around Fionna's relationship with the cool, brooding vampire Marshall Lee, who is a gender swapped version of herself.
name: Bad Little Boy

description:
Plot Summary

When Marceline invites the Ice King to play basketball with them, Finn and Jake become confused. They confront her about it, and she decides to tell them the truth about her history with the Ice King.
name: Simon & Marcy

description:
Plot Summary

Becoming increasingly insecure about his relationship with Flame Princess, Finn starts to feel low and builds himself a pillow fort. While seeking solace in the fort, he falls into a strange dream, in which he awakens in another world populated by strange pillow people.
name: Puhoy

deck: A BMO solo adventure
description:
Plot Summary

After an accident separates them from Finn and Jake, BMO must overcome obstacles and the perils of impromptu babysitting to return home. When the situation looks bleak, will BMO succumb to sorrow or will a new friend give hope?
name: BMO Lost

description:
Plot Summary

Finn and Jake decide to see how long they can go without speaking, using only written signs to communicate. But, unaware of the situation and convinced that they have been replaced by impostors, BMO becomes confused and afraid.
name: Shh!

description:
Plot Summary

There is a long line of suitors, anxious to date Princess Bubblegum. Annoyed at her lack of interest, the Gumball Guardians ask Peppermint Butler to intervene.
name: The Suitor

description:
Plot Summary

Saddened by his unrequited feelings for Princess Bubblegum, Ice King runs away to a desert island, where he makes an unusual new friend.
name: The Party's Over, Isla de Senorita

description:
Plot Summary

Marceline needs to recover something very dear to her from a witch, but can't do it without some help from Princess Bubblegum.
name: Sky Witch

description:
Plot Summary

Inspired by a strange dream he has after a confrontation between the two, Finn tries to set up a fight between Flame Princess and Ice King, using underhanded tactics. But all does not go according to plan.
name: Frost & Fire

description:
Plot Summary

Finn and Princess Bubblegum attend an official function in Lemongrab's kingdom, and are appalled at what they find there. Together, they come up with a plan to change things for the better.
name: Too Old

deck: While walking home from the movies after watching "Star: Dog Ranger of the North Woods" twice, Shaggy and Scooby-Doo discover a lone black suit of armor in the driver's seat of a pickup truck, and the gang delivers it to the local museum. The kids later break into the museum to search for clues, thinking that the archaeologist who was transporting the suit may be missing, and learn that the knight has come to life.
name: What a Night for a Knight

deck: Side-tracked by a giant bat, the gang helps the Three Stooges with their theme park: a real-life ghost town with real-life ghostly villains.
name: Ghastly Ghostly Town

deck: The kids suspect an old ghost in a green-glowing sea-diver suit is connected with the disappearance of several boats.
name: A Clue for Scooby-Doo

deck: Mystery Inc. teams up with Batman and Robin to uncover a counterfeiting ring run by a strange hooded figure who has been sending counterfeit money to the Joker and the Penguin.
name: The Dynamic Scooby-Doo Affair

deck: When the Mystery Machine gets stuck in the mud, Mystery Inc. ends up becoming housekeepers for the Addams Family while Gomez and Morticia go on vacation. When a giant vulture threatens the house and Wednesday goes missing, it's up to Scooby-Doo and the gang to rescue her and stop the Vulture.
name: Wednesday is Missing

deck: Jonathan Winters invites the gang to stay with them on a chicken farm, where Maude Frickert needs help finding a secret formula unless a mysterious scarecrow gets to it first.
name: The Frickert Fracas

deck: Stuck in a storm, the kids take shelter in a nearby mansion, where everybody — even the ghosts — seem to think the kids are someone else.
name: Guess Who's Knott Coming to Dinner

deck: After returning the dog of Phyllis Diller, Mystery inc investigates a gargoyle after her treasure which leads them all to the magic mansion where there is a hoax set up in order to trick Phyllis Diller into revealing the location of her treasure.
name: A Good Medium is Rare

deck: Mystery Inc. comes to the aid of Sandy Duncan when various monster attacks disrupt the production of her latest movie.
name: Sandy Duncan's Jekyll and Hyde

deck: Mystery Inc. stays at an offshore hotel with Sonny & Cher when the hotel manager Mr. Meekly warns them of the Shark God Pescado Diabolico and his Shark Men.
name: The Secret of Shark Island

deck: Mayhem ensues in the western town of Juneberry when the fog rolls in.
name: The Spooky Fog of Juneberry

deck: The ghost of Bigfoot has been scaring everyone away from a popular skiing resort. Scooby's gang, together with Laurel and Hardy, try to solve the mystery.
name: The Ghost of Bigfoot

deck: Scrambler is a former OCP member who turned into a criminal and now he is in the prison.He manage to hack into RoboCop's control system and he programs RoboCop to break him out from the prison.The final plan is to destroy OCP and the Old Man with the help of the brainwashed RoboCop.
name: The Scrambler

deck: OCP's scientists create an energy absorbing monster which escapes from the lab through the sewers.A counter with the Deathspore makes RoboCop ill and it's seems like nothing can stop the huge electric beast.
name: Project Deathspore

deck: The Three Stooges are in danger when Curly-Joe takes up a crop-dusting job on a farm haunted by the ghost of Manfred von Richthofen.
name: The Ghost of the Red Baron

deck: Mystery Inc. and the Harlem Globetrotters encounter a mysterious ship manned by ghost pirates.
name: The Ghostly Creep from the Deep

deck: Davy Jones is the heir to Hagglethorn Hall, a haunted fortress that was brought over from Scotland. But a phantom knight doesn't want him to take it over, so the kids help him solve the mystery.
name: The Haunted Horseman of Hagglethorn Hall

deck: Scooby and the gang go to hear a concert by Jerry Reed but discover he is missing and are told by Big Bing and Bertha to leave the place because everything is fine. Not satisfied, they sneak in through a window.
name: The Phantom of the Country Music Hall

deck: Mystery Inc. teams up with Batman and Robin when Professor Flaky is kidnapped by Joker and Penguin.
name: The Caped Crusader Caper

deck: Inviting the Harlem Globetrotters to Shaggy's uncle's house, the gang gets caught between colonial ghosts, and a sea serpent.
name: The Lochness Mess

deck: While intending to go on a trip to Picnic Island, the gang and the Harlem Globetrotters end up on a boat going to the nearby Haunted Island where they are greeted by three hooded ghosts.
name: The Mystery of Haunted Island

deck: While en route to the Tom Sawyer festival, the gang gets lost during a storm and wind up getting stuck on dock near an old haunted showboat, the Dixie Queen, where they bump into Josie and the Pussycats, who were slated to perform there. But as they try to ride out the storm and at the same time restore the vessel, they find out that there are ghosts on board who want to sink those plans.
name: The Haunted Showboat

deck:
There is a new gang in Old Detroit called The Brotherhood and their misson is to get rid of all robots.They using EMP bombs to make the robots go crazy.The people of Old Detroit starts protesting, because they don't fell sefe in the city anymore.
The Brotherhood's final plan is to detonate a huge EMP bomb which will effect the whole towns robotic population.
name: The Brotherhood

deck: Dexter becomes an exchange student to Japan and releases a monster.
name: Last But Not Beast

deck: Jeannie brings Mystery Inc. along for a time-travel trip to help stop Jadal the Evil Djinn's plan to thwart a young prince's elevation to sultan.
name: Mystery in Persia

deck: The gang help coach Tim Conway track down the ghost of an athlete that is haunting the students and faculty of Velma's alma mater.
name: The Spirit Spooked Sports Show

deck: Mystery Inc. helps out Don Adams when he is hired to exterminate the bugs in the home of known horror movie actor Lorne Chumley. It becomes even difficult as there are monsters around each corner.
name: The Exterminator

deck: The gang team up with the Speed Buggy crew to find out why a town's population is suddenly declining, as they learn that something is strangely blowing in the wind and its causing the residents to be fearful.
name: The Weird Winds of Winona

deck: Answering the cries of The Mamas and the Papas singer Cass Elliot, Mystery Inc. find themselves trying to unmask the Green Globs who are running amok in her candy factory.
name: The Haunted Candy Factory

deck: Mystery Inc. arrives at a carnival run by Dick Van Dyke and assist him when a Ghostly Strongman ends up haunting it.
name: The Haunted Carnival

deck: The gang goes out on a boating expedition, but get lost in a fog and runs aground on Haunted Isle. They decide to venture to the abandoned Vázquez Castle on the island for help, but instead encounter a transparent phantom who threatens them to leave the island and never return. The gang tries to capture him, resulting in a number of problems and hi-jinks.
name: Hassle in the Castle

deck: Thanks to Shaggy's poor map reading, the sleuths end up in Gold City, a ghost town inhabited by the Miner 49er, a ghost who is in search of the last vein of gold, and each night the mine moans, calling for the miner and scaring away everyone but the gang, who want to know what's going on.
name: Mine Your Own Business

deck: When a rash of local dognappings alarms prize-winning dog trainer Buck Masters, the gang offers to have Scooby-Doo pose as a decoy to catch the dognappers. However, their plan works too well as Scooby is himself dognapped, leading the gang to discover that the dognappers appear to be under the command of a ghastly Native American witch doctor.
name: Decoy for a Dognapper

deck: The kids pay a visit to their friend Sharon Weatherby, whose Uncle Stuart is being haunted by the ghost of Elias Kingston. When Stuart disappears altogether, Mystery, Inc. ventures into the abandoned and allegedly haunted Kingston Mansion in search of him and the ghost. Things take a turn for the worse when Uncle Stuart appears to be first aged by the ghost, and then turned into a skeleton.
name: What the Hex Going On?

deck: The gang gets jobs as extras on the set of Daphne's Uncle Maxwell's movie set "The Apeman of Forbidden Mountain." Legend has it that a real apeman is haunting the set, and Uncle John's movie is in jeopardy of not being finished.
name: Never Ape an Ape Man

deck: Two water people find Aang, an air nomad in an iceberg.
description:
Overview

While fishing, Sokka and Katara discover Aang and his flying bison Appa icebound floating on the sea. After freeing him, they discover that Aang is an Airbender from the Air Nomads, a race of people assumed to have died out a hundred years before. When he goes with them to the water tribe he doesn't reveals that he is the Avatar that bends the four elements. The Avatar is reincarnated generation after generation and would be the only one who could prevent the Fire Nation from conquering all the nations, which is why the Fire Nation exterminated the Air Nomads. Meanwhile, Zuko, the banished Prince of the Fire Nation, is patrolling the seas in search of the Avatar. While exploring an abandoned Fire Nation ship, Katara tells Aang about the war that had been going on for the past hundred years. They accidentally set off a light beam in the ship, which alerts Zuko to the village.

Introduction

Long ago, the legendary Avatar kept the world and its four nations at peace with each other. However, the Avatar disappeared one hundred years ago and has not been seen since. During that time, the tyrannical Fire Nation used the opportunity to wage war with the other three nations, seeking to conquer them. One hundred years passed and people began to lose hope that the Avatar would ever return and bring peace back to the world. Even the Southern Water Tribe, located in the distant South Pole sea, has been affected by the Fire Nation's war. The men of the tribe all sailed abroad to fight, leaving behind the women and children. Sokka and his younger sister Katara are the oldest of the tribe's children in the South Pole.

Synopsis

Two siblings, Katara and Sokka, are out fishing in a small canoe. Katara, a waterbender, practices her bending as Sokka prepares to spear a fish. Katara bends the water around a fish to lift it above the canoe; Sokka penetrates the water bubble with the back of his spear, causing the fish to fall back into the water and soak him. He grows angry and scolds Katara, saying that if he had "weird powers" he would keep his "weirdness" to himself. When the sea currents suddenly pick up speed, Sokka tries to steer the boat to avoid colliding with the small chunks of floating ice, while Katara gives directions. However, the boat is crushed between two ice floes, leaving Sokka and Katara stranded in the middle of the sea on a floating chunk of ice. Sokka blames Katara for the mess, which causes her to lose her temper and start yelling at him.

As Katara rages, she ends up violently waterbending without realizing it; soon, she cracks and shatters an ice formation, revealing a giant glowing orb of iceberg which rises to the surface of the ocean. Seeing the form of a human inside the ice, Katara thinks the person needs help and begins chopping away at the iceberg with Sokka's club despite his warning not to, as they do not know who the "thing" is. The ice breaks and releases a bright column of light into the sky.

Prince Zuko, a Fire Nation teenager who has been hunting the Avatar for two years, sees the bright light from his ship. His uncle, Iroh, who has accompanied the young prince on his journey, dismisses the event as completely natural. Zuko orders his crew to head toward the light, insisting that the light was emitted due to the Avatar.

After Katara breaks through the ice, she finds the person is a young boy with strange arrow-like marks on his head and hands. Sokka is skeptical and points his spear at the boy, but the boy simply falls down into Katara's arms. She lays him down and tries to help him. Sokka pokes the boy in the head with the blunt side of his spear, still skeptical, but Katara shoos him away.

The mysterious boy drowsily opens his eyes to see Katara staring at him with deep blue eyes. He quickly becomes fully dazzled, cheerfully asking Katara if she wants to go penguin sledding with him, to which she confusedly agrees. The boy introduces himself as Aang before sneezing, sending himself high into the air and drifting back down unharmed. Katara realizes that he must be an airbender.

Aang climbs back into the ice to find Appa, a large flying bison. It takes a moment for Aang to wake him up. Appa sneezes on Sokka and covers him with bison snot, to which Sokka reacts with disgust. The warrior does not believe that the bison can actually fly and walks away, only to realize that he is stranded in the middle of the sea and cannot go back home. Aang offers to fly them back to the Southern Water Tribe where they live. Katara happily agrees and Sokka refuses at first, but agrees later as he has no choice. The group gets on Appa's saddle, with Sokka still refusing to believe that Appa can fly. Aang cries, "Yip-Yip!", causing Appa to leap into the air, but he comes crashing right back down into the water and starts swimming. Aang figures Appa is still too tired to fly just yet. He turns around and stares at Katara with a huge smile on his face, causing her to ask, "Why are you smiling at me like that?" He replies, "Oh, I was smiling?" Sokka lifts his head back, groaning, while Katara, at first smiling at Aang's response, frowns back at him. After some time, Katara tells Aang that the last Avatar was supposed to be an Air Nomad and asks if Aang knew him. Aang awkwardly states that he knew people that knew the Avatar, but did not know the actual Avatar himself.

Later, Aang has a dream about a storm that he and Appa had encountered while they were near the South Pole. He re-lives the dream how both of them were brought under the waves by the intense wind and rain, and how Aang started glowing and created the orb of ice that surrounded him. He is jolted awake, finding himself awakened by Katara in a tent in the Southern Water Tribe. He quickly gets dressed with Katara watching. She notices the arrow markings running along his body, and after he is completely dressed, she pulls him into the village to introduce him to the entire village, which has a small population.

Everyone expresses surprise at seeing an airbender, as no one has seen an Air Nomad in a hundred years, thinking they must have become extinct. Sokka wonders why Aang always carries a staff around, realizing it is not sharp enough to stab anybody. Aang responds by showing the village how he uses airbending to fly with it. Aang ends up accidentally crashing into Sokka's poorly-constructed watch tower.

Kanna, also known as Gran Gran, the grandmother of Katara and Sokka, wonders if Aang may be a threat to the tribe. Katara wants him to stay, believing he could teach the village so many good things as well as waterbending to her. They happen to glance over at Aang, who is showing off to the village toddlers how he can stick his tongue to his staff.

On the Fire Nation ship, Prince Zuko is practicing his firebending techniques with Uncle Iroh as his mentor. Zuko becomes impatient and asks for his uncle to teach him advanced moves, but Iroh demands that he first master the basics. However, after Zuko's angry persistence, he finally consents.

Sokka begins to teach the young boys of the tribe, lecturing them about how they are the "warriors" of this tribe, until one of them says innocently he needs to pee. Sokka gets mad at Aang for distracting his "warriors" with fun and games and throws a fit because they should be focused on the ongoing war. When Aang sees an otter penguin, he gets excited and tries to capture it, but the creature proves to be too fast and slippery. Katara approaches and agrees to teach him the "fine art" of catching penguins in exchange for lessons in waterbending. However, Aang points out that he knows nothing about waterbending, being an airbender, and tells her that she could learn from the other people in the tribe. Katara responds that she is the only waterbender in the whole South Pole.

Aang says that the Northern Water Tribe should have waterbenders to teach Katara and offers to fly her to the North Pole. Katara is not sure whether leaving her tribe is a good idea. Aang suggests to her that she could think about it later, and in the meantime she could teach him to catch penguins. Thus, Katara begins her "lessons" to Aang.

Aang and Katara go penguin sledding and have fun until they accidentally slide near an old abandoned shipwreck. Aang wants to go in and explore it, but Katara is wary. She has been told never to go onto the Fire Navy ship, but Aang convinces her to do so. As they explore the ship, Aang wonders why a Fire Nation ship is so far from its home. Katara realizes Aang has no knowledge of the Hundred Year War at all and deduces that he was trapped in the iceberg for one hundred years. They accidentally set off a booby trap in the ship, sending off a flare into the sky. Aang saves Katara by carrying her and airbending out of the ship. However, Prince Zuko has seen the flare and Aang escaping from the ship and believes he has found the long lost Avatar – at last.
name: The Boy in the Iceberg
